1.4
log
@Many fixes after some actual testing:

- fix two syntax errors (forgotten ;;) in upkg_get_file
- add z to tar flags (oops)
- fix a strange syntax error in the awk part
- add support for @@ignore directive
- change one instance of $localbase -> $LOCALBASE

With the result, I was able to install the mircksum package on MirPorts on
Mac OS.

TO DO:

- (maybe) check if you need root privileges
- simple dependency handling
- support for @@sample filename
- support for @@exec
- (maybe) a verbose flag
- (maybe) package deletions or even info
@
